    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/f1717-noncannulated-yield-force",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force QoI comparison — combined laboratories",
      "description": "FEA predicted yield force 6.8% below experimental mean; within the pre-specified 10% bound. E/uval = 1.31 < 1.96. Morris screening conducted during the UQ campaign confirmed that screw cross-section geometry tolerance (±0.05 mm) contributes negligibly (<3%) to yield-force variance, supporting the decision to fix nominal geometry in the deterministic submission model."
    },
