      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted (coarse: 142k elements, medium: 387k elements, fine: 1.02M elements). Richardson extrapolation applied. Grid Convergence Index: stiffness 1.2%, yield force 1.8%, force at 40 mm 1.4%. All GCI values well below 5% threshold. Achieved level 3 due to systematic extrapolation approach."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals < 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) used. Force residual norm converged to 1e-8 at every load increment. Energy balance monitored across all 200 sub-steps; maximum imbalance 0.03%. Achieved level exceeds required minimum."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments by a second qualified analyst.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a senior analyst not involved in original model development. Boundary conditions, contact definitions, material assignments, and load application verified against the ASTM F1717 test protocol. One minor discrepancy in rod pre-tension magnitude corrected prior to submission runs. Final model signed off by both analysts."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that continuum elasto-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening is appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V screw under quasi-static bending. Literature support required.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model for Ti-6Al-4V validated against uniaxial coupon data from three material batches (R² = 0.994). Large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM ON) activated. Frictionless-to-frictional contact transition captured via augmented Lagrangian method. Model form selection supported by Nagaraja et al. (2021) and three additional peer-reviewed studies of metallic spinal implant FEA."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties derived from coupon testing of same material batch as test constructs. Geometric inputs from CMM measurement of production screws.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus derived from tensile coupon tests (N=9, same Ti-6Al-4V batch as test constructs). Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements (±0.01 mm). The UQ campaign (Sobol analysis, 2048 quasi-Monte Carlo samples) confirmed cortical bone block modulus and screw-rod friction coefficient as the two dominant sensitivity drivers (combined first-order Sobol index 0.71). Distributions for these parameters were informed by published literature ranges and propagated through the ensemble to generate prediction intervals reported in the ValidationResult narratives."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 test constructs from production lots; traceability of components documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5). All screws and rods from production lots with full traceability documentation (lot numbers, inspection certificates). UHMWPE bone block material certificates provided. Sample size meets the pre-specified minimum of N=10."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing at multiple loading rates and/or environmental conditions to bound clinical variability. Minimum two distinct test conditions required at Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717. Clinical loading rates span a broader range; only one test condition evaluated. This factor is below the required level. Risk is partially mitigated by the conservative nature of quasi-static testing relative to dynamic fatigue, but the gap is acknowledged as a limitation of the current validation dataset. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) traceable to and consistent with experimental test conditions.",
      "rationale": "One-to-one mapping documented between FEA inputs and experimental measurements: screw geometry from CMM of test-lot screws, bone block modulus from published UHMWPE coupon data, clamp boundary conditions replicating F1717 fixture geometry. Traceability matrix reviewed and approved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and QoI difference < 10% for all three quantities of interest.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria simultaneously: stiffness (4.2%, E/uval=0.87), yield force (6.8%, E/uval=1.31), force at 40 mm (3.1%, E/uval=0.54). Validation uncertainty uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Annex B incorporating experimental measurement uncertainty and numerical uncertainty from GCI analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to structural performance endpoints relevant to clinical failure modes (stiffness loss, plastic deformation onset, large-displacement load capacity).",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs post-operative load sharing and adjacent segment mechanics. Yield force corresponds to onset of permanent deformation, a direct precursor to implant fatigue failure. Force at 40 mm displacement characterises post-yield energy absorption relevant to trauma loading. All three QoIs are clinically and biomechanically motivated and directly observable in the F1717 test."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (F1717 compression-bending, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, UHMWPE bone block) is the same scenario as the COU. No extrapolation required.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity is identical to the COU: same screw design, same rod diameter, same ASTM F1717 test configuration, same UHMWPE bone block surrogate. No geometric, material, or loading extrapolation is required. This is a direct validation with maximum relevance to the COU."
    }
