    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and accepted on the basis that quasi-static F1717 testing is the regulatory standard for this device class and that the three primary QoIs all satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria with E/uval well below 1.96. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the submission claim for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
